pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants; Chemical resistant gloves made of polyvinyl chloride (PVC) ≥ 14 mils, nitrile rubber ≥ 14 mils, or butyl rubber ≥ 14 mils; Shoes and socks

Active_Ingredients.name: Prothioconazole
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Demethylation inhibitor (DMI) class of fungicides; FRAC Group 3 fungicide

Safety_Information.general_Info: Harmful if swallowed or inhaled. Avoid breathing vapor or spray mist. Causes moderate eye irritation. Avoid contact with eyes and clothing. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco, or using the toilet. Remove and wash contaminated clothing before reuse.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing eye. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Immediately call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. Do not induce vomiting unless told to do so by a poison control center or doctor. Do not give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Take off contaminated clothing. Rinse skin immediately with plenty of water for 15-20 minutes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Inhaled: Move person to fresh air. If person is not breathing, call 911 or an ambulance, then give artificial respiration, preferably mouth-to-mouth if possible. Call a poison control center or doctor for further treatment advice.
